-- 02_revenue_by_channel_city.sql
```sql
WITH customer_primary_channel AS (
    SELECT 
        customer_id,
        channel,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY customer_id ORDER BY attributed_at ASC) as rn
    FROM customer_channels
),
channels AS (
    SELECT 
        customer_id,
        channel
    FROM customer_primary_channel
    WHERE rn = 1
)
SELECT 
    COALESCE(c.channel, 'Unattributed') AS channel,
    COALESCE(s.city, 'Unknown') AS city,
    SUM(t.amount) AS total_revenue,
    COUNT(t.transaction_id) AS transaction_count,
    COUNT(DISTINCT t.customer_id) AS unique_customers
FROM transactions t
JOIN customers cu ON t.customer_id = cu.customer_id
LEFT JOIN channels c ON t.customer_id = c.customer_id
LEFT JOIN stores s ON t.store_id = s.store_id
GROUP BY c.channel, s.city
ORDER BY total_revenue DESC;
